Package: npTrend
Type: Package
Title: Trend Estimation with Bootstrap Inference for Parametric and Nonparametric Trends in Climate Time Series
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Marina", "Friedrich", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "m.friedrich@vu.nl", comment = "Author on paper, author of code in package"),
    person("Richard", "Bao", email = "r5bao@uwaterloo.ca", role = c("aut"), comment = "Package developer"),
    person("Stephan", "Smeekes", role = "ctb", email = "s.smeekes@maastrichtuniversity.nl", comment = "Author on paper"),
    person("Eric", "Beutner", role = "ctb", email = "e.beutner@vu.nl", comment = "Author on paper")
  )
Maintainer: The package maintainer <m.friedrich@vu.nl>
Description: Provides tools for parametric and nonparametric trend estimation and inference in time series data. 
    Implements the methods described in Friedrich et al. (2020) <doi:10.1007/s10584-020-02806-2> for 
    detecting trends, estimating simultaneous confidence bands, and testing for monotonicity 
    and linearity. Features include autoregressive wild bootstrap (AWB) inference and 
    modified cross-validation (MCV) for bandwidth selection.
